Intel Corp's McAfee to Acquire Stonesoft Oyj
Monday, 6 May 2013 09:41am EDT
McAfee, a wholly owned subsidiary of Intel Corp announced the execution of a definitive agreement to initiate a conditional tender offer for the acquisition of Stonesoft Oyj a innovator innetwork firewall products, for an aggregate equity value of approximately $389 million in cash. Stonesoft delivers software-based, dynamic, customer-driven, cyber security solutions to secure information flow and simplify security management. Stonesoft`s product portfolio of firewalls, evasion prevention systems, and SSL VPN solutions addresses businesses of all sizes. Through the pending acquisition of Stonesoft, McAfee expects to extend its leadership position in network security.Â 
